data.title: Marius Toime | People - K&L Gates
data.snippet:
Marius is a member of the Sustainable Energy Association of Singapore and is a committee member of the Corporate Practice Committee of the Law Society of Singapore, which addresses matters relating to corporate practice in Singapore. He sits on the Climate Change Focus Group of the British Chamber of Commerce in Indonesia and is a member of the ESG Working Group of the Law Society of Singapore. Formerly a non-executive director of community charity, We Care Community Services Limited and chair of the Built Environment Committee of the British Chamber of Commerce in Singapore. Marius actively participates as a pro bono legal advisor for community law.

Marius regularly participates in webinars and other events, including invitations to present at the following recent webinars: [...] Marius is a strategic advisor valued for his ability to navigate complex negotiations and offer commercially focused, pragmatic advice. He is recognized for his grasp of the commercial drivers behind transactions, his understanding of deal dynamics, and for crafting workable solutions that help close deals. [...] Marius has advised on a broad spectrum of corporate finance transactions, distressed transactions convertible or exchangeable bonds, pre-export finance transactions, and sale and leaseback transactions. He has substantial experience in Indonesia, having both lived and worked there as a qualified Foreign Legal Consultant (Konsultan Hukum Asing). He is dual-qualified in England and Singapore, giving him the flexibility to operate effectively across multiple jurisdictions.

Mariusâ€™ sector experience includes carbon solutions (carbon capture, trading and energy transition), data centers and energy-intensive infrastructure, ESG, renewables, oil and gas, LNG, energy finance, offshore wind energy, power generation and transmission, manufacturing and distribution, and maritime.
